#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Āhāravagga "
msgstr "2. Fuel "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Moḷiyaphaggunasutta → phagguno (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Moḷiyaphaggunasutta "
msgstr "12. Phagguna of the Top-Knot "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.13, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.12:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ vā anuggahāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four fuels. They maintain sentient beings that have been born and help those that are about to be born. "

msgctxt "sn12.12:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn12.12:1.4"
msgid "Kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr "Solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention the third, and consciousness the fourth. "

msgctxt "sn12.12:1.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ vā anuggahāyā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four fuels that maintain sentient beings that have been born and help those that are about to be born.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: moḷiyaphagguno → moḷiyaphagguṇo (si) | moliyaphagguno (s1-3, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.12:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Phagguna of the Top-Knot said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.2"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, viññāṇāhāraṃ āhāretī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, who consumes the fuel for consciousness?” "

# NOTE: BB’s “valid” is a little too specifically logical.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.12:2.3"
msgid "“No kallo pañho”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“That’s not a fitting question,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.12:2.4"
msgid "“‘āhāretī’ti ahaṃ na vadāmi. "
msgstr "“I don’t speak of one who consumes. "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.5"
msgid "‘Āhāretī’ti cāhaṃ vadeyyaṃ, tatrassa kallo pañho: "
msgstr "If I were to speak of one who consumes, then it would be fitting to ask "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.6"
msgid "‘ko nu kho, bhante, āhāretī’ti? "
msgstr "who consumes. "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.7"
msgid "Evañcāhaṃ na vadāmi. "
msgstr "But I don’t speak like that. "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ maṃ avadantaṃ yo evaṃ puccheyya: "
msgstr "Hence it would be fitting to ask: "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.9"
msgid "‘kissa nu kho, bhante, viññāṇāhāro’ti, esa kallo pañho. "
msgstr "‘Consciousness is a fuel for what?’ "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.10"
msgid "Tatra kallaṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ: "
msgstr "And a fitting answer to this would be: "

msgctxt "sn12.12:2.11"
msgid "‘viññāṇāhāro āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbattiyā paccayo, tasmiṃ bhūte sati saḷāyatanaṃ, saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Consciousness is a fuel that conditions rebirth into a new state of existence in the future. When that which has been reborn is present, there are the six sense fields. The six sense fields are a condition for contact.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.12:3.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, phusatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, who contacts?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.12:3.2"
msgid "“No kallo pañho”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“That’s not a fitting question,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
